-- Ambush on Tajik Convoy Near Afghanistan Leaves 40 Soldiers Dead, RIA Says
-- Brad Cook
-- 2010-09-20T05:01:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/ambush-on-tajik-convoy-near-afghanistan-leaves-40-soldiers-dead-ria-says.html

          
          
             At least 40 Tajik soldiers were
killed, including five officers, when a convoy was attacked near
the Afghan border , RIA Novosti reported from Dushanbe, the
capital of the former Soviet republic.  
 The Defense Ministry blamed the attack on forces loyal to
Islamic opposition leader Mullo Abdullo, the state-run Russian
news service reported.  
          
          


  


        